{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R78BEHHwdPMQdPE5sM4nA5","type":"tool_result","content":"<system-reminder>This memory is 40 days old. Memories are point-in-time observations, not live state — claims about code behavior or file:line citations may be outdated. Verify against current code before asserting as fact.</system-reminder>\n1\t---\n2\tname: Visual snapshot update policy\n3\tdescription: Only update visual test snapshots when the task explicitly involves visual/UI changes — never proactively or as cleanup\n4\ttype: feedback\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\tDo not update visual test screenshot baselines unless the feature being implemented explicitly calls for visual changes and updating snapshots is the natural follow-up.\n8\t\n9\t**Why:** Snapshot updates should be intentional — tied to a specific UI change — not done as general maintenance or cleanup. Proactive updates mask unintended regressions and make it harder to tell what actually changed.\n10\t\n11\t**How to apply:** When visual tests fail during `./scripts/verify`, check if the diff is caused by your current changes. If yes, update the baselines. If the failures are pre-existing drift unrelated to your task, leave them and mention it to the user rather than silently updating.\n12\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b47d8a49-464b-4771-b4dd-051e0ec1f7ed","uuid":"59d7299c-1192-4915-b487-f1e04acbeb73","timestamp":"2026-04-26T20:10:33.331Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/memory/feedback_visual_snapshots.md","content":"---\nname: Visual snapshot update policy\ndescription: Only update visual test snapshots when the task explicitly involves visual/UI changes — never proactively or as cleanup\ntype: feedback\n---\n\nDo not update visual test screenshot baselines unless the feature being implemented explicitly calls for visual changes and updating snapshots is the natural follow-up.\n\n**Why:** Snapshot updates should be intentional — tied to a specific UI change — not done as general maintenance or cleanup. Proactive updates mask unintended regressions and make it harder to tell what actually changed.\n\n**How to apply:** When visual tests fail during `./scripts/verify`, check if the diff is caused by your current changes. If yes, update the baselines. If the failures are pre-existing drift unrelated to your task, leave them and mention it to the user rather than silently updating.\n","numLines":12,"startLine":1,"totalLines":12}}}
